comment.body:
> When there are errors `verify_callback()` can be called multiple times per file. eg Multiple failed pieces in the one file. 

Does it? I thought the error callback will only be called for the first piece that errored, because `file_valid` will be set to false here:

https://github.com/transmission/transmission/blob/0f321b850342646c8ca3fd5e54a75220e34865cf/libtransmission/verify.cc#L140

And so the file won't be added to `files_ending_in_current_piece` for the pieces afterwards.

> I could make it one callback per file with a vector of errors but it makes the `verify_torrent()` logic more complicated. It doesn't help that a piece can contain multiple files.

No no, that's not what I want either. In that case, how about you initialise `current_index` to `~0` instead of `0`, and set `status.index` to `index` instead of `current_index` inside `verify_callback()`?

```cpp
// Before
tr_file_index_t current_index;
// After
tr_file_index_t current_index = ~0;

// Before
status.index = current_index;
// After
status.index = index;
```

